title: Live - BMC Election 2017 Results: Who will win?
text:
Shiv Sena's Arundhati Dudhwadkar, Surendra Bagalkar are leading 10:43 AM (IST) Akash Raj Purohit, son of BJP MLA Raj Purohit, leading 10:41 AM (IST) We have fought BMC election on a positive note which is development oriented Govt: Shaina NC, BJP #MumbaiDecides pic.twitter.com/p5ialmCvZ5 &:mdash; TIMES NOW (@TimesNow) February 23, 2017 10:39 AM (IST) &:mdash; TIMES NOW (@TimesNow) February 23, 2017 10:35 AM (IST) Positive about our winning; Both brothers (Raj & Uddhav Thackeray) can't come together: Manohar Joshi, Senior Shiv Sena leader told ANI 10:28 AM (IST) The first leads are in. The BJP and the Shiv Sena both lead in one seat each. 10:06 AM (IST) Counting of votes for 227 wards of BMC begins in Mumbai 
Counting has begun in the BMC polls that will decide who gets to govern Mumbai for the next five years. The battle, this time, is between the Shiv Sena and the BJP which decided against an alliance. We’re getting you the latest here. 09:59 AM (IST) Missing names the new 'swing factor' in this BMC election 
The large number of missing names from electoral lists could impact the three top parties’ performance significantly, party leaders said on Wednesday, as they prepared to file formal complaints with the Election Commission and demand an inquiry to pin responsibility for the goof-up. According to some estimates, nearly 12 lakh voters’ names were missing, which is over 13 per cent of the 91 lakh registered voters. In municipal elections, where seats are won and lost by margins as small as 500 votes, the missing voters could become a new swing factor. Read more here... 09:52 AM (IST) Shiv Sena has won BMC elections consistently for over two decades now 09:13 AM (IST) Stats to keep in mind 09:12 AM (IST) Pruned voters' list pushes up turnout 
While the city takes pride in its highest ever voter turnout – 55.53 per cent – for a municipal election, here’s a reality check. The 11 per cent jump from 2012 is thanks in part to the fact that the revised voters’ list this year had 11 lakh people less than in 2012. Read more here... 08:42 AM (IST) This is what politicians did on the eve of results 
After a gruelling, month-long campaign, contestants and sitting corporators spent the gap day cooking, hitting the gym and simply being at home with their loved ones. Read more here... 08:17 AM (IST)
